<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t17430907-26">
               <interp inst="t17430907-26" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17430907-26" type="year" value="1743"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17430907-26" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17430907"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17430907-26" type="date" value="17430907"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17430907-26-off137-c203" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-26-defend254 t17430907-26-off137 t17430907-26-verdict140"></join>
         
               <p>399. 
               
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-defend254" type="defendantName">
                     Philip 
                     Jones 
                  <interp inst="t17430907-26-defend254" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-defend254" type="given" value="Philip"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-defend254" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , of <placeName id="t17430907-26-defloc136">St James, Westminster</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17430907-26-defloc136" type="placeName" value="St James, Westminster"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17430907-26-defloc136" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-26-defend254 t17430907-26-defloc136"></join>, was indicted for <rs id="t17430907-26-off137" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-off137" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-off137" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing a Silver Spoon, value 10 s.
            </rs> the Goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-victim256" type="victimName">
                     Robert 
                     Champion 
                  <interp inst="t17430907-26-victim256" type="surname" value="Champion"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-victim256" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-victim256" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-26-off137 t17430907-26-victim256"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17430907-26-cd138" type="crimeDate">Aug. 25</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-26-off137 t17430907-26-cd138"></join>.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-person257">
                  Robert 
                  Champion 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person257" type="surname" value="Champion"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person257" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person257" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 25th of August, I lost a Silver Spoon out of my Kitchen; this is the Spoon.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-person258">
                  Edward 
                  Wakelyn 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person258" type="surname" value="Wakelyn"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person258" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person258" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t17430907-26-viclabel139" type="occupation">Silversmith</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-26-victim256 t17430907-26-viclabel139"></join>. I stopped this Spoon and the Prisoner; he brought it to me the 24th of August to sell; but seeing a Crest upon it, I asked him how he came by it; he said, what was that to me; so I secured him; and then he said, he bought it of a Woman in the Strand. He did not produce the Woman, neither did he know her Name. - He was very much in Liquor, when he brought it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-person259">
                  James 
                  Bromley 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person259" type="surname" value="Bromley"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person259" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person259" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The Prisoner served his Time in the Country; he lived with me ten Months as a Journeyman. I took him on the Recommendation of Sir 
               <persName id="t17430907-26-person260">
                  Watkin 
                  Williams 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person260" type="surname" value="Williams"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person260" type="given" value="Watkin"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person260" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and during that Time he behaved very well; his Friends have the best of Characters in Wales.</p>
               <p>- . I am a Brewer, I have known the Prisoner 18 Years, he has been entrusted with 50 or 60 l. at a Time in the Room where he lay, and I never heard that he ever wronged any body before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-person261">
                  John 
                  Bromfield 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person261" type="surname" value="Bromfield"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person261" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , 
               <persName id="t17430907-26-person262">
                  Richard 
                  Farrel 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person262" type="surname" value="Farrel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person262" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person262" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , and 
               <persName id="t17430907-26-person263">
                  Richard 
                  Graham 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person263" type="surname" value="Graham"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person263" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person263" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , have known him about a Year, and believe him to be a very honest young Man.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17430907-26-person264">
                  Elias 
                  Jones 
               <interp inst="t17430907-26-person264" type="surname" value="Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person264" type="given" value="Elias"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-person264" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , (Cousin to the Prisoner.) He is about 22 Years of Age, I have known him eighteen Years. I never knew any Thing amiss of him; they are a very honest Family, all the whole Generation are so. <rs id="t17430907-26-verdict140" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-verdict140" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-verdict140" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17430907-26-punish141" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-punish141" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17430907-26-punish141" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="whipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17430907-26-defend254 t17430907-26-punish141"></join>
               
                     <note>[Whipping. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
